dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Taylor b Mills 115 (144b 12x4 2x6 185m) SR: 79.86

dismissalComment.html: Fine knock comes to an end. It was the low full toss and Hafeez tries to whip it over the on side field but top edges it to the on side. Rosco, at midwicket, moves to his left to take it. Good knock from Hafeez. His maiden ton. Just ahead of the WC. Purrfect timing.

Pakistan look so good when the top order gives them a solid base and the dangerous men lurking in the lower order are given a free licence to hit. That's how they played in 80's. dismissalText.long: c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Hafeez
dismissalText.commentary: Scott Styris c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Hafeez 46 (67b 1x4 0x6 80m) SR: 68.65

dismissalComment.html: Nice catch from Umar Akmal. Is that the game-breaking blow? Styris connected with the slog sweep and the white ball seemed to be soaring over midwicket boundary. Umar stationed himself just inside the boundary, hopped back to reach above him and plucked it. He then looks back to see whether his feet are safe inside the line. They are. Out!

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson b Wahab Riaz 42 (63b 1x4 0x6 77m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Castled! It was the slower one, on the middle, from a back of length, Kane had to wait on that front foot, he then tried to swat it across the line but edged it back on to his stumps

Caught or grounded? is the question. Replays suggest it was a clean catch . Guptill has to go, after he gets confirmation from the third umpire. Guptill pressed back to punch it away from the body and Shehzad dived forward full towards the ball at point to pouch it. Smart catch. 80 for 3 and NZ are wobbling here. The umpires have told the batsman to wait. They go upstairs. Shehzad dived forward, caught the ball cleanly above the ground and the question is when he landed did the ball touch the ground. But the right palm came under the ball at that point and the ball doesn't seem to have touched the ground. Out!

headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: moves outside leg and heaves this leg break over the midwicket boundary where its caught by a fan, who pockets the ball!

commentPostTextItems.html: Pakistan have completed a crushing win to level the series. Afridi applauds his team-mates' efforts before shaking hands with the opposition. What a fiery knock it was from Afridi. Please hang on for quotes from the post-match ceremony.

Taylor: "The last ten overs .. they got the runs and in the end we couldn't keep up with the rate. We got a few starts but didn't go on. All credit to them; Umar Gul bowled well. The pitch broke up a bit in the end; it was dry and abrasive, Gul and Wahab Riaz got some reverse swing. You got to give credit to Afridi who hit some massive sixes."

Afridi: "The way Hafeez started; he played like an experienced player. Misbah and Hafeez took the responsibility to ensure that we played 50 overs. We played mature cricket. In the end, we and Razzaq go like playing Twenty20 cricket. Nothing happenned with the ball in the first 20 overs. Hafeez and Misbah took time; we had wickets in hand and we could play the big shots. Umar Gul is bowling well, in Tests and ODIs. Tanveer, Wahab are doing perfect jobs. "

Man of the match is Hafeez: "We were all looking forward to win this game and I am happy. I was just concentrating and thinking of spending more time out there. The team was looking to level the series; it was a good team effort."
That's it from us. Thanks for logging on. Good bye and Good luck.

commentTextItems.html: Yet another one of those swing and misses. Kamran collects again.
full delivery on the pads, rolls away to third man .. shout for lbw but that was going down the leg
yorker on the middle, the batsman moved outside leg and managed to slice it to third man
Ooh .. it missed the off stump but not by much. Again, the same routine from the batsman - move to the leg and swing in hope

commentPreTextItems.html: Rob Lamb: "For a player that is rated so highly by Dan Vettori and seen as an essential part of the one day team - Jacob Oram has a fairly disappointing average. Certainly he has delivered on occasion but with an average of only 24 after 143 matches it is hard to see why he is considered such a lynch pin. Perhaps the sad reality is that there is no one better waiting in the wings! "

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c Mills b Oram 12 (22b 1x4 0x6 47m) SR: 54.54

dismissalComment.html: gone! What was Younis doing there? He appeared to have made his mind up there, came down the track before it was delivered and failed to pick the change in pace, it was the slower one, went through with his attempted loft over mid-on, mistimed and was caught comfortably

headshotImage.caption: Scott Styris player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Styris player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c Styris b Mills 35 (64b 1x4 0x6 91m) SR: 54.68

dismissalComment.html: Misbah falls, trying to force the pace. He went down the track and tried to clear  the length delivery over mid-off but didn't connect well. Styris pouches it at mid-off

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Taylor b Mills 115 (144b 12x4 2x6 185m) SR: 79.86

dismissalComment.html: Fine knock comes to an end. It was the low full toss and Hafeez tries to whip it over the on side field but top edges it to the on side. Rosco, at midwicket, moves to his left to take it. Good knock from Hafeez. His maiden ton. Just ahead of the WC. Purrfect timing.

headshotImage.caption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal b Bennett 44 (29b 4x4 2x6 51m) SR: 151.72

dismissalComment.html: shuffles across to outside off and tries to paddle it but misses. The off stump is pegged back. Good hand from Umar, though. Pakistan look so good when the top order gives them a solid base and the dangerous men lurking in the lower order are given a free licence to hit. That's how they played in 80's. And they continue to do it in some style even now

headshotImage.caption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Hamish Bennett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c †McCullum b Bennett 65 (25b 5x4 5x6 26m) SR: 260

dismissalComment.html: Fine catch from Brendon. It was the good-length delivery cutting into Afridi who went for the pull but got an inside edge. Baz dives to his left to pluck it with his left hand. Murderous innings from Afridi ends. It was immense fun to watch.

dismissalText.long: c Ahmed Shehzad b Wahab Riaz
dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill c Ahmed Shehzad b Wahab Riaz 39 (39b 4x4 2x6 68m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Caught or grounded? is the question. Replays suggest it was a clean catch . Guptill has to go, after he gets confirmation from the third umpire. Guptill pressed back to punch it away from the body and Shehzad dived forward full towards the ball at point to pouch it. Smart catch. 80 for 3 and NZ are wobbling here. The umpires have told the batsman to wait. They go upstairs. Shehzad dived forward, caught the ball cleanly above the ground and the question is when he landed did the ball touch the ground. But the right palm came under the ball at that point and the ball doesn't seem to have touched the ground. Out!

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c Younis Khan b Umar Gul 6 (14b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: Younis takes a neat catch at first slip. It was a probing delivery that landed on a good length outside off and straightened. Rosco got forward to defend and ended up stabbing it to left of Younis who lunges low to pouch it.

dismissalText.long: c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Hafeez
dismissalText.commentary: Scott Styris c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Hafeez 46 (67b 1x4 0x6 80m) SR: 68.65

dismissalComment.html: Nice catch from Umar Akmal. Is that the game-breaking blow? Styris connected with the slog sweep and the white ball seemed to be soaring over midwicket boundary. Umar stationed himself just inside the boundary, hopped back to reach above him and plucked it. He then looks back to see whether his feet are safe inside the line. They are. Out!

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson b Wahab Riaz 42 (63b 1x4 0x6 77m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Castled! It was the slower one, on the middle, from a back of length, Kane had to wait on that front foot, he then tried to swat it across the line but edged it back on to his stumps

headshotImage.caption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendon McCullum run out (Umar Akmal) 12 (13b 1x4 0x6 21m) SR: 92.3

dismissalComment.html: Brendon is run out It was pushed to right of backward point and they went for the risky single. Direct hit has Brendon out by a meter.. Umar Akmal is thrilled as he dashes off towards his team-mates. Brendon is pretty angry and upset as he storms off
